Three men charged with allegedly poaching a rhino for its horn at a game farm near Grahamstown last year will make a second bid for bail next month. Police allege they caught Jabulani Ndlovu, 39, Forget Ndlovu, 36, and Sikhumbuzo Ndlovu, 37, in a chalet at Grahamstown s Makana Resort last year with a 10.27kg freshly harvested rhino horn, valued at close to R1-million.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.